description.et:
Term paper (2000 words)
Maximum points to earn: 30 (A = 27 or above, E = 18 or below, see criteria above)
Assessment scale:
17 points or below (corresponds to E) - the form is, in general, in compliance with the requirements and correct; references are minimal and insecure; the elements of analysis and independent interpreting are there; the coverage of the subject is, in general, logical, but the connections are full of gaps;
18-20 points (corresponds to D) - the form is in compliance with the requirements and, in general, correct; references are minimal, but relevant; the analysis and independent interpreting is understandable, but at times insecure; the coverage of the subject is logical and associated;
21-23 points (corresponds to C) - the form is in compliance with the requirements and correct; references are relevant and sufficient; analytical connections and interpretations are proper and there is certainty in creating connections; the treatment of the subject is logical, but there are some weaknesses from the point of view of the whole;
24-26 points (corresponds to B) - the form is excellent; the choice, amount and association of references with the text is very good; thorough analysis of connections and references; bold interpretation based on connections; the treatment of the subject as a whole is logical and smooth;
27 points or above (corresponds to A) - the form is excellent; the choice, amount and association of references with the text is creative; the depth of the analysis and the level of independent interpretation is remarkable; the connections are thorough-going and creative; the treatment of the subject is innovative and logical; the text is a remarkable achievement on the whole.
Maximum total points: 30
